      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SYDNEYSIDER (3) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 320m at Richmond, taking a Grade 5 in a fast 18.21. Rates a top chance if runs up to time two back. HARD STYLE GIRL (7) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a half a length win at Nowra in a handy 20.83. Draws out wide but goes well over this trip. Winner at her latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. SNOOPY'S ETHICS (1) has missed the frame at his last two but did run well three back when third (25.26) in a Grade 5 at Maitland. Has the ability and expected to do much better. ASHES TO ASHES (2) drops in distance and warrants respect.",
